metadata.name: Olive Aluminium Xenon #64
metadata.description:
"Olive Aluminium Xenon" explores using generative backgrounds to lead a field of isometric shapes. How the foreground and background interact varies wildly from generation to generation. Some generations resemble mountain ranges or mesas, some crystal fields or cityscapes. 

"Olive Aluminium Xenon" was created with p5.js.

metadata.name: Medusa #31
metadata.description:
“Nunc, o fortissime, fare, precor, Perseu, quanta virtute quibusque artibus abstuleris crinita draconibus ora!” - Ovid, Metamorphoses Book IV 769
"Perseus, I beg you to tell us by what prowess and by what arts you carried off that head with snakes for hair."

Medusa is built in 3D with p5.js using physics of oimo.js (see LICENSE.md). 

For high resolution renderings (4x resolution of current canvas size): Open the artwork in its own browser tab, add the parameter '&highres=4' to the url and reload. e.g. https://gateway.fxhash2.xyz/ipfs/<something>/?fxhash=ooXrQmk42nyJd4HAB63v7jJ9R27DiwcbwDaUEYuX3FvGDzfwNog&highres=4 .

For endless waves: Open the artwork in its own browser tab, add the parameter '&infinity=true' to the url and reload. e.g. https://gateway.fxhash2.xyz/ipfs/<something>/?fxhash=ooXrQmk42nyJd4HAB63v7jJ9R27DiwcbwDaUEYuX3FvGDzfwNog&infinity=true .

For an export as .PNG press 'e'.

I am afraid that's all there is to say.

Stefan Schwaha, @sektionschef, https://digitalitility.com/

metadata.name: Gerhard #331
metadata.description:
Gerhard is a collaboration of Richard Nadler and Leander Herzog on fxhash. A generative animation based on multiple layers of color and data, mixed, moved and painted over in realtime. Some fragments stick to the canvas while others get discarded to leave the existing layers visible, allowing a complex surface to emerge and build up over time. 
Richard Nadler created the textures to control composition and color. Leander Herzog created the code for the interplay between the layers, motion and interactions. Both artists use different tools and are not aware of the details of each others process, meeting through the interface of pixels. This collaboration is enabled by twitter and fxhash, as the generative art community continues to explore abstraction in summer 2022 – while extreme temperatures, wildfires, ongoing conflicts and volatile markets continue to escalate. 

- Click to start a new layer of motion and color. 
- Doubleclick to enter fullscreen mode. 
- Press “s” to save the current canvas. 
- Append ?dpr=4 to the url to increase the resolution.

https://leanderherzog.ch/2022/gerhard/

metadata.name: JullyCar #72
metadata.description:
We all dream of having a car or we have

Some of us even talk to our car

And some of us see our car like a cartoon character.

This collection is not only an NFT but also a match
If you win one of the cups, in addition to a Super Rare edition, there are also prizes for the owners in the Primary market, which you can find on our Twitter ( @Morixels )

To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

This project is a collaboration project and it is a Benefit for the owners of the most Morixels to Collaborate with Morixels Designer.

metadata.name: Garden, Monoliths #104
metadata.description:
"Garden, Monoliths" is the result of an algorithm that started in April 2021. It was called "Grass.js".
Spring was blooming all around the house, taking over the stones and remnants of ancient battles that stood here. Inspiration was everywhere.
The initial goal was to use mathematical formulas for creating patterns inspired by the density of nature, that could be used by a pen plotter, so it kept focusing on outputting vector lines. This history and practice produced a graphical style based on line strokes, plus occasionally some transparent, filled shapes.
Each artwork will be either "Garden" or "Monolith", for they are variations of two existing designs from the workshop.

metadata.name: Cappadocia Dream #1
metadata.description:
Cappadocia Dream is a generative art project by James Filomar. It is the artist’s depiction of hot air balloons hovering above the majestic rocky terrain of Cappadocia.

metadata.name: FxPlanet #161
metadata.description:
🟢〰Storyline〰🟢

Once upon a time, a God had a little daughter. The daughter liked to explore the planets on his father's cosmos. Suddenly the daughter got sick and died like a collapsing star. God gets alone, angry, depressed and finally mad. He turned all the universe to ash and mixed the ash of her daughter's soul with it to make her alive, But he failed. In the end, he decided to destroy himself to make a New cosmos of all generative planets from ash of himself and his daughter's soul to one more time in the eternity they can be with each other in a heart of a planet. If you listen carefully to the planets, you may hear them calling each other.

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🔴〰Rarity〰🔴

This collection is a 3D generative interactive artwork (Made with Unity Game Engine) that contains of 9999+1 planets (1 shared source of light and 9999 pieces of souls) from billions of variation. You can see more random variations from fxhash page.
◼ The beauty and complexity of the Planet's surface is important, But what is going on inside?
Each planet has three grades of volume (High, Medium, Low) that show you what resources exist on the planets (Common, Rare, Legendary).
Some resources are so valuable and infrequent.
◼ For Example: It's possible to get Oxygen (Legendary Resource) on Low volume slot, but it's infrequent if you get it on High volume slot.
◼ Checkout Material rarity list on webpage.

📎 Webpage address: HashProtocol.tez.page

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🔵〰Social〰🔵

◼ Participant in events or get achievements to win some prizes.
So it's significant to see you on the discord server. Checkout rarity table, achievements rewards, … on the webpage.
📎 Webpage address: HashProtocol.tez.page

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🟠〰Interact〰🟠

◼ You can rotate around of planets by “WASD” keys on the keyboard or arrow keys.
◼ Zoom In by “E” key and Zoom Out by “Q”.
◼ Full HD texture by Key “1”.
◼ 4k texture by Key “2”.
◼ 8k texture by Key “3”.
